in background )

270
00:16:41,166 --> 00:16:42,250
Henderson:
- MASTER MACKY...

271
00:16:42,333 --> 00:16:43,291
Sylia:
- CHILDREN...

272
00:16:46,833 --> 00:16:49,333
Nene:
- OKAY, I CREATED THIS SYSTEM

273
00:16:49,416 --> 00:16:51,708
BUT IT'S BEEN A WHILE
SINCE I DEBUGGED IT.

274
00:16:51,791 --> 00:16:54,833
HM, I'M AFRAID IT MAY BE
GETTING TOO LARGE

275
00:16:54,916 --> 00:16:57,166
FOR THE SIZE OF THE BUS.

276
00:16:57,250 --> 00:17:01,125
OF COURSE, IF I PUT A REPEATER
HERE AT THE BRIDGE

277
00:17:01,208 --> 00:17:03,583
THE OVERALL RESPONSE RATIO OUGHT
TO BE IMPROVED A LITTLE BIT.

278
00:17:03,666 --> 00:17:05,166
AT LEAST FOR THE MOMENT.

279
00:17:05,250 --> 00:17:08,041
- OH, I SEE. THAT MAKES SENSE.
I DIDN'T KNOW WHAT TO DO

280
00:17:08,125 --> 00:17:11,041
WHEN THE CIRCUITS FOR SYLIA
AND PRISS GOT DOUBLED UP,

281
00:17:11,125 --> 00:17:15,041
I SURE COULD HAVE USED YOU THEN.

282
00:17:15,125 --> 00:17:16,041
- ( both shout )

283
00:17:22,958 --> 00:17:24,791
- HEY, WAIT. I THINK
YOU SHOULD HAVE

284
00:17:24,875 --> 00:17:27,625
TO FIGURE THESE THINGS
OUT FOR YOURSELF.

285
00:17:27,708 --> 00:17:31,458
AND ANYWAY, I HAVE A LOT OF
MORE IMPORTANT THINGS TO DO

286
00:17:31,541 --> 00:17:32,500
THAN BABYSITTING YOU.

287
00:17:32,583 --> 00:17:33,500
- OKAY.

288
00:17:37,375 --> 00:17:39,541
- BUT YOU CAN STILL
ASK ME QUESTIONS.

289
00:17:39,625 --> 00:17:42,500
- THANK YOU, NENE.

290
00:17:42,583 --> 00:17:43,583
- ( scowls )

291
00:17:43,666 --> 00:17:46,000
- MA'AM!

292
00:17:48,083 --> 00:17:50,000
- ( both laughing )

